Kinda got extorted. Entrance fee is criminal. For 6 hours, ended up paying almost as much as I did for 12 hours in Yala with brekkie and lunch included. So it goes. Absolutely pouring, had/forced to leave the park at 830 due to severe flash flooding. Ended up birding the roads around the park (included in this list). Non avian highlight was a rouge elephant that tried to run the car off the road.--I honestly can’t believe I had such a high species total given the rain (and frankly my low effort). I didn’t think I would’ve broke 60 until I started making the checklist. I imagine that on a nicer day with more of a concerted effort towards passerines, 120 would be quite possible in a morning.
